SQL Injection
fields.description: Code injection technique,  in which nefarious SQL statements are inserted into application  incorrectly filtered inputs.

fields.name: Command Injection
fields.description: A technique used via a web interface in order to execute OS commands on a web server.

fields.name: Cross-site Scripting (XSS)
fields.description: A type of security vulnerability that allows attackers to inject client-side scripts (usually JavaScript) into web pages viewed by other users.

fields.name: Cross-site request forgery (CSRF)
fields.description: A type of malicious exploit where unauthorized commands are transmitted from a user that the web application trusts.

fields.name: Denial of Service (DoS)
fields.description: A attack where the perpetrator seeks to make a machine or network resource unavailable to its intended users by temporarily or indefinitely disrupting services of a host connected to the Internet.

fields.name: Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS)
fields.description: A type of Denial of Service, where the incomming traffic originates from multiple sources..

fields.name: Slowloris
fields.description: A type of denial of service attack, which allows a single machine to take down another machine's web server with minimal bandwidth and side effects on unrelated services and ports. It's done by opening connections to the target web server and sending a partial request in a attempt to keep many connections to the target web server open and hold them open as long as possible.

fields.name: Buffer Overflow
fields.description: A type of attack, witch takes advantage of an anomaly where a program, while writing data to a buffer, overruns the buffer's boundary and overwrites adjacent memory locations to insert malicious code.
